  "doc_id": "1589",
  "text": "(3) Scours on the leeside edge of the geotextile mattress. The sand-pass opening below the plate is not only a path for sediment transportation, but it is a source of high velocity bottom flow as well. Xie and Liu [CITATION_1] detected high velocity flow through the sand-pass opening through numerical simulation. The excessive flow through the opening may extend beyond the mattress on the leeside and trigger scour on the leeside edge of the GMSP. In Fig 16, the scour hole on the leeside of the GMSP can be observed after 20 minutes' flow. The scour is highly likely to be caused by the high velocity flow through the gap between the sloping plate and the mattress. As the scour hole gets deeper, the barrier slowing down the seepage under the mattress is removed and the critical value of i m also gets reduced. Xie et al [CITATION_2] reckoned that the opening ratio should be strictly controlled below a specific value to prevent the scour of this kind.",
